Day 6 — Permissions and Access Control
Permission Model
Artifactory has a hierarchical permission model:

Users → Groups → Permission Targets → Repositories

Entities
Users — individual accounts. Can be:

Local (managed in Artifactory)
LDAP/Active Directory synced
SAML SSO
Service accounts (for CI/CD)
Groups — collections of users. Assign permissions to groups, not individual users (scalable).

Permission Targets — define what operations are allowed on which resources.

Repository Permissions
A Permission Target specifies:

Which repositories it applies to
Which users/groups it grants access
What operations they can perform

Permission	Meaning
Read	Download artifacts, view metadata
Annotate	Add/edit artifact properties
Deploy/Cache	Upload artifacts to local repos; cache to remote repos
Delete/Overwrite	Delete artifacts or overwrite existing ones
Manage	Manage the repository itself
Manage Local Repos	Create/edit local repos
Manage Remote Repos	Create/edit remote repos

Access Tokens
Recommended for CI/CD authentication instead of username/password:

User tokens — scoped to a specific user
Project tokens — scoped to a JFrog Project
Reference tokens — short-lived, automatically rotated
Can be restricted to specific repos and operations
Projects
JFrog Projects provide multi-tenancy — isolate teams within a single Artifactory instance:

Each project has its own repositories, users, and quotas
Platform admins manage the overall system
Project admins manage their own team's resources
